# Jaza Venus Project Goals

Read [docs/project-goals.md](docs/project-goals.md) for full context. Enforce:

## Must-have goals

- **G1** Full feature migration — parity matrix shows no required gaps before cutover
- **G2** Zero workflow breakage — preserve legacy labels from `frontend/src/app/modules.tsx`
- **G3** Fast and secure — follow security and performance docs
- **G4** Complete data migration — schema-mapping and ETL stay aligned
- **G5** Production cutover — Phase 1 UAT passes per cutover checklist

## Improvements (do not revert to legacy)

I2 one-step invoice, I3 RBAC, I4 audit trail, I5 i18n (id default), I7 web access.

## Non-negotiable business rules (§5)

- Document chain: PO→GRN; SO→Delivery→Invoice→Payment
- P1/P2/P3 discounts; credit plafond + overdue blocking with admin override
- Stock: Available = OnHand − Committed
- Faktur Pajak serial pool for PKP customers
- Payments: Cash, Transfer, Check/Giro, Others, Return, Adjustment
- Division scoping on all queries
- Status: legacy O/B/C vs new Draft/Posted/Voided — map correctly

## Do

- Prefer Phase 1 cutover blockers over Phase 3 polish
- Reuse existing Application services and `businessRuleFlow.ts` before inventing rules
- Preserve user-facing legacy screen titles unless PRD explicitly changes them

## Don't

- Invent business rules not in PRD, BRD §2, or legacy reference
- Rename navigation labels to “modern” English without approval
- Mark features done when only API or UI shell exists
